<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
<A NAME="eolPage37"></A>
<DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	CSX CORPORATION
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	PART II
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:13PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:13PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Revenue
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	In 2015, revenue decreased $858 million, or seven percent, mostly due to the decline in fuel surcharge of $646 million. Additionally, the decline in volume of two percent and unfavorable mix were partially offset by pricing strength.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Merchandise
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Agricultural
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;PADDING-LEFT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Agricultural and Food Products
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;- Volume declined due to challenging world market conditions and a strong U.S. dollar. Specifically, high levels of imported ethanol reduced rail moves to Eastern markets and the strong dollar hampered export grain competitiveness. Additionally, excess truck capacity led to lower shipments of food products. These declines were partially offset by strength in feed grain and domestic soybean moves, reflecting the record 2014-2015 harvest.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;PADDING-LEFT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Fertilizers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;- Volume was down, reflecting weak demand driven by oversupply of fertilizer, low corn prices and a challenged export market due to strength of the U.S. dollar.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Industrial
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;PADDING-LEFT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Chemicals
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;- Volume was flat as strong gains in LPG and petroleum products were offset by the slowdown in crude oil and frac sand due to low oil prices and the conclusion of major waste remediation projects.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;PADDING-LEFT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;PADDING-LEFT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Automotive
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;- Volume increased as gains in auto movement, especially SUVs and trucks, resulted from strong North American light vehicle production and consumer demand.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;PADDING-LEFT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;PADDING-LEFT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Metals and Equipment
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;- Volume declined primarily due to high levels of steel imports which resulted from the strength of the U.S. dollar and led to lower production of domestic steel.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Housing and Construction
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;PADDING-LEFT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Minerals
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;- Volume growth reflects strength in aggregates (which include crushed stone, sand and gravel) due to increased highway and non-residential construction activity.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;PADDING-LEFT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;PADDING-LEFT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Forest Products
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;- Volume declines reflect high inventories of building products in the housing sector as well as declining demand due to electronic substitution in paper products.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Coal
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;PADDING-LEFT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Domestic
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	- Volume declined as a result of mild weather, high stockpiles and low natural gas prices favoring natural gas power generation.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:0PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;PADDING-LEFT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Export
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	- Reductions in both metallurgical and thermal coal volume resulted from ongoing weak market conditions due to global oversupply and the strength of the U.S. dollar.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Intermodal
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:0PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;PADDING-LEFT:54PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Domestic
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	-
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;Domestic volume increased 12 percent due to customer growth, continued success with CSX&#8217;s highway-to-rail conversion program and new service offerings.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:0PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:0PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;PADDING-LEFT:54PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	International
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	- Competitive losses resulted in a five percent international volume decline during a volatile year marked by West Coast port disruption, a subsequent volume surge and then a weak peak season.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Other
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Other revenue increased $56 million as a result of higher revenue from customers who did not meet
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:0PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;PADDING-LEFT:6PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	minimum contractual volumes as well as higher incidental revenue.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
	CSX 2016 Form 10-K p.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
	&#32;37

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	CSX CORPORATION
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	PART II
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:13PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:13PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Expense
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:0PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;PADDING-LEFT:6PX;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	In 2015, total expenses decreased $829 million, or nine percent, compared to prior year. Descriptions of each expense category as well as significant year-over-year changes are described below.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:0PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:4PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;PADDING-LEFT:6PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Labor and Fringe
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;expenses include employee wages and related payroll taxes, health and welfare costs, pension, other post-retirement benefits and incentive compensation. These expenses decreased $87 million due to the following items:
</FONT>
</DIV>
<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN; FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:102PX;">
</TD>
<TD>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP">
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:11PT;PADDING-LEFT:54PX;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#8226;
</FONT>
</DIV>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP;">
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Inflation resulted in $128 million of additional cost driven by increased wages partially offset by reduced health and welfare costs.
</FONT>
</DIV>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<A NAME="FIS_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE_19"></A>

</TD>

</TD>

<TR>
<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP">

<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#8226;
</FONT>
</DIV>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP;">
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Incentive compensation was $97 million lower reflecting reduced award payouts on existing plans.
</FONT>
</DIV>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN; FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

</TD>

<TR>
<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP">
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:11PT;PADDING-LEFT:54PX;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#8226;
</FONT>
</DIV>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP;">
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Efficiency savings of $84 million were primarily a result of reduced crew starts due to the Company's train length initiatives, lower operating support costs and reduced management headcount.
</FONT>
</DIV>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>

	Volume-related costs were $66 million lower.

</TD>

</TD>

<TR>

</FONT>
</DIV>

<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP;">
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Various other costs increased $30 million.
</FONT>
</DIV>

</TR>

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:0PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:4PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;PADDING-LEFT:8PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Materials, Supplies and Other
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;expenses consist primarily of contracted services to maintain infrastructure and equipment, terminal services at automotive facilities and professional services. This category also includes costs related to materials, travel, casualty claims, environmental remediation, train accidents, property and sales tax, utilities and other items. Total materials, supplies and other expenses decreased
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;PADDING-LEFT:8PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$148 million driven by the following:
</FONT>
</DIV>
<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN; FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:102PX;">
</TD>
<TD>

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:4PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;PADDING-LEFT:6PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">

	Fuel
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;expense includes locomotive diesel fuel as well as non-locomotive fuel. This expense is largely driven by the market price and locomotive consumption of diesel fuel. Fuel expense decreased $659 million driven by the following:
</FONT>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN; FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;expense primarily relates to recognizing the costs of a capital asset, such as locomotives, railcars and track structure, over its useful life. This expense is impacted primarily by the capital expenditures made each year. Depreciation expense increased $57 million due to a larger asset base.
</FONT>

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:10PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Equipment and Other
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;includes rent paid for freight cars owned by other railroads or private companies, net of rents received by CSXT for use of its equipment. This category of expenses also includes lease expenses for locomotives, railcars, containers and trailers, offices and other rentals. These expenses increased $8 million driven by the following:
</FONT>
</DIV>
<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN; FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<TR>

	Inflation resulted in $16 million of additional cost related to rates on automotive and intermodal cars.
</FONT>
</DIV>

	Interest Expense
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;decreased $1 million to $544 million due to lower average interest rates partially offset by higher average debt balances.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:4PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;PADDING-LEFT:6PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Debt Repurchase Expense
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;decreased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$16 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;associated with costs incurred in 2014 related to the early redemption of long-term debt did not repeat in the current year.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:4PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:4PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Other Income (Expense)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	&#32;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	-
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	&#32;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	net
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;increased $122 million to $98 million primarily due to a $59 million gain on a sale of non-operating easements and a reimbursement of environmental costs of $21 million related to this sale. Additionally, 2015 environmental costs were $21 million lower than 2014.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:0PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:4PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Income Tax Expense
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;increased $53 million to $1.2 billion primarily due to higher earnings as well as prior year favorable state legislative changes that did not repeat in the current year.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:0PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:4PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Net Earnings
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;increased $41 million to $2.0 billion, and earnings per diluted share increased $0.08 to $2.00 due to the factors mentioned above. Lower average shares outstanding resulting from higher share repurchase activity also had a positive impact on earnings per diluted share.
</FONT>
</DIV>

<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:9PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	FRA Personal Injury Frequency Index
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
	&#32;- Number of FRA-reportable injuries per 200,000 man-hours.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:9PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	FRA Train Accident Rate
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
	&#32;- Number of FRA-reportable train accidents per million train-miles.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;PADDING-LEFT:49PX;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:9PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	On-Time Train Originations
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
	&#32;- Percent of scheduled road trains that depart the origin yard on-time or ahead of schedule.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;PADDING-LEFT:49PX;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:9PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	On-Time Destination Arrivals
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
	&#32;- Percent of scheduled road trains that arrive at the destination yard on-time or earlier to two hours late (30 minutes for intermodal trains).
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;PADDING-LEFT:49PX;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:9PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Dwell
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
	&#32;- Average amount of time in hours between car arrival at and departure from the yard. It does not include cars moving through the yard on the same train.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;PADDING-LEFT:49PX;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:9PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Train Velocity
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
	&#32;- Average train speed between terminals in miles per hour (does not include locals, yard jobs, work trains or passenger trains).
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;PADDING-LEFT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:9PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Cars-On-Line
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
	&#32;- An average count of all cars on the network (does not include locomotives, cabooses, trailers, containers or maintenance equipment).
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	The Company measures and reports safety and service performance.&#160; The Company strives for continuous improvement in these measures through training, innovation and investment. CSX's safety and train accident prevention programs rely on the latest tools, programs and employee participation that are designed to continuously strengthen the safety culture. Increased investment in training and technology also is designed to allow CSX employees to have an additional layer of protection that can detect and avoid many types of human factor incidents. The Company's safety programs are designed to prevent incidents that can adversely impact employees, customers and communities.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Continued capital investment in the Company's assets, including track, bridges, signals, equipment and detection technology also supports safety performance. CSX has established formal relationships with industry groups, leading universities and suppliers to develop, implement and deploy the latest technology that can detect infrastructure problems before they happen. To illustrate, through a waiver granted by the FRA, CSX is using advanced continuous rail testing methods that are being adopted by other railroads as the system&#8217;s value is proven.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	The Company constantly collaborates with the FRA and industry organizations as well as federal, state and local governments on safety innovations and initiatives. For example, CSX and other freight railroads have actively worked with the U.S. DOT and other key stakeholders to evaluate and implement far-reaching safety enhancements for transportation of certain flammable materials, including essential energy products, on the nation&#8217;s freight railroad network.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#160; &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
	CSX 2016 Form 10-K p.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
	&#32;40
</FONT>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
<A NAME="eolPage41"></A>
<DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	CSX CORPORATION
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	PART II
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	At CSX, operational success is built on employee commitment to maintaining a constant focus on safety. Although the number of FRA reportable personal injuries decreased 10 percent year-over-year, the FRA reportable personal injury frequency index increased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	9 percent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;to 1.02 due to a 17 percent decrease in labor hours versus 2015. While the reported FRA train accident frequency rate has remained flat year-over-year at
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	2.62
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, both overall FRA train accidents and train miles have decreased 14 percent year-over-year.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:0PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	The Company made strong improvements to network reliability and service measures in 2016 while delivering a record level of productivity
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;On-time originations improved 25 percent year-over-year to 84 percent, and on-time arrivals increased 27 percent year-over-year to 65 percent. Terminal dwell remained flat at 25.7 hours versus 2015 and average train velocity increased one percent to 20.8 miles per hour.
</FONT>
</DIV>
</EFX_RESULTS_OF_OPERATIONS>
<DIV>
<A NAME="CSX-12302016X10K_HTM_S0A7A2E6B506A54E285FD0612CC905F99">
</A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:13PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:13PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<EFX_LIQUIDITY_CAPITAL>
<A NAME="FIS_LIQUIDITY_CAPITAL"></A>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:13PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:13PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	LIQUIDITY AND CAPITAL RESOURCES
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Liquidity is a company&#8217;s ability to generate adequate amounts of cash to meet both current and future needs for obligations as they mature and to provide for planned capital expenditures, including those to address regulatory and legislative requirements.&#160;&#160;To have a complete picture of a company&#8217;s liquidity, its balance sheet, sources and uses of cash flow and external factors should be reviewed.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Material Changes in the Consolidated Balance Sheets and Significant Cash Flows
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Consolidated Balance Sheets
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	CSX's balance sheet reflects its strong capital base and the impact of CSX's balanced approach in deploying capital for the benefit of its shareholders, which includes investments in infrastructure, dividend payments and share repurchases.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Total assets as well as total liabilities and shareholders' equity
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	increased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$669 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;from prior year. The increase in assets was driven by higher net properties of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$976 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;resulting from capital investments, partially offset by payments of about $300 million made on debt related to assets purchased in 2015 under seller financing. The increase in total liabilities and shareholders' equity combined was driven by an increase in net borrowings of about $450 million (including payments made on debt for assets purchased in 2015 under seller financing) and an increase in deferred income tax liabilities of $417 million. Partially offsetting these increases was a reduction in other long-term liabilities due to voluntary pension contributions of $250 million.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Significant cash flows
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	The following charts present net cash provided by (used in) operating, investing and financing activities for full years 2014, 2015 and 2016.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<IMG SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2017/02/14/0000277948-17-000009_CSX-1230201_CHARTX42508.JPG" ALT="CSX-1230201_CHARTX42508.JPG" STYLE="HEIGHT:220PX;WIDTH:220PX;">
<IMG SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2017/02/14/0000277948-17-000009_CSX-1230201_CHARTX43373.JPG" ALT="CSX-1230201_CHARTX43373.JPG" STYLE="HEIGHT:220PX;WIDTH:220PX;">
<IMG SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2017/02/14/0000277948-17-000009_CSX-1230201_CHARTX44267.JPG" ALT="CSX-1230201_CHARTX44267.JPG" STYLE="HEIGHT:220PX;WIDTH:220PX;">
</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">

<A NAME="eolPage42"></A>
<DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	CSX CORPORATION
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	PART II
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Sources of Cash
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	The Company has multiple sources of cash.&#160; First, the Company generates cash from operations. In
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, the Company generated
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$3.0 billion
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;of cash from operating activities which was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$329 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;lower than prior year primarily driven by $250 million in voluntary contributions to the Company's qualified pension plans. In 2015, the Company generated
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$3.4 billion
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;of cash from operating activities which was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$27 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;higher than 2014 primarily driven by higher collections of freight account receivables.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Second, CSX has access to numerous financing sources including a $1 billion five-year unsecured revolving credit facility that expires in May 2020.&#160; As of the date of this filing, the Company has no outstanding balances under this facility.&#160;&#160;See Note 9, Debt and Credit Agreements for more information.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Third, CSX filed a new shelf registration statement with the SEC in February 2016 which is unlimited as to amount and may be used to issue debt or equity securities at CSX&#8217;s discretion, subject to market conditions and CSX Board authorization. While CSX seeks to give itself flexibility with respect to cash requirements, there can be no assurance that market conditions would permit CSX to sell such securities on acceptable terms at any given time, or at all.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Uses of Cash
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	CSX continued to invest in its business to create long-term value for shareholders. In
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, net cash used in investing activities was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$1.8 billion
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, a decrease of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$1.1 billion
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;from the prior year primarily driven by lower net purchases of short-term investments and lower property additions. In 2015, net cash used in investing activities was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$2.9 billion
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, an increase in net investing of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$709 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;from 2014 primarily driven by fewer net sales of short-term investments.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	The Company is committed to maintaining and improving its existing infrastructure and to positioning itself for long-term growth through expanding network and terminal capacity. Funds used for property additions are further described below.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>

<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#160;

</TD>
<TD COLSPAN="11" STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:BOTTOM;BORDER-BOTTOM:2PX SOLID #000000;PADDING-LEFT:2PX;PADDING-TOP:2PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:2PX;">
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Fiscal Years
</FONT>
</DIV>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:BOTTOM;BORDER-BOTTOM:2PX SOLID #000000;PADDING-LEFT:2PX;PADDING-TOP:2PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:2PX;PADDING-RIGHT:2PX;">
<DIV STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Capital Expenditures
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	(Dollars in Millions)
</FONT>

	Total capital expenditures shown above include investments related to reimbursable public-private partnerships. These partnership investments are for projects that are partially or wholly reimbursed to CSX through either government grants or other funding sources such as cash received from a property sale.&#160; These reimbursements may not be fully received in a given year; therefore the timing of receipts may differ from the timing of the investment.&#160;
</FONT>

<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
<A NAME="eolPage43"></A>
<DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	CSX CORPORATION
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	PART II
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Planned capital investments for 2017 are expected to be
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$2.2 billion
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, including about
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$270 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;for PTC. This
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$2.2 billion
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;excludes investments related to partially or wholly reimbursable public-private partnerships where reimbursements may not be fully received in the year the reimbursement obligation arises. Approximately half of the 2017 investment will be used to sustain the core infrastructure. The remaining amounts will be allocated to locomotives, freight cars and high return projects supporting long-term profitable growth, productivity initiatives and service improvements to optimize performance. CSX intends to fund capital investments through cash generated from operations.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	The Company expects to continue incurring significant capital costs in connection with the implementation of PTC. CSX estimates that the total multi-year cost of PTC implementation will be approximately $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	2.4 billion
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	. This estimate includes costs for installing the new system along tracks, upgrading locomotives, adding communication equipment and developing new technologies. Total PTC spending through 2016 was $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	1.8 billion
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	In addition to capital investments, the Company uses cash for scheduled payments of debt and leases, share repurchases and to pay dividends to shareholders.&#160;In 2016, net cash used in financing activities was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$1.3 billion
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, which represents an increase in spending of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$749 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;from the prior year primarily driven by the repayment of seller-financed assets, higher share repurchases, and lower net debt issued. In 2015, net cash used in financing activities was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$519 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, which represents a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	decrease
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;in spending of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$564 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;from the prior year primarily driven by higher net long-term debt issued of $904 million (net of lower debt repayments) partially offset by higher share repurchases of $287 million.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	CSX is continually evaluating market and regulatory conditions that could affect the Company&#8217;s ability to generate sufficient returns on capital investments.&#160; CSX may revise its future estimates for capital spending as a result of changes in business conditions, tax legislation or the enactment of new laws or regulations which could have a material adverse effect on the Company&#8217;s&#160;operations and financial performance in the future (see Risk Factors under Item&#160;1A of this Form 10-K).
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Liquidity and Working Capital
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Currently, CSX is well positioned from a liquidity standpoint.&#160; The Company ended the year with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$1.0 billion
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;of cash, cash equivalents and short-term investments. CSX has a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$1 billion
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;unsecured, revolving credit facility backed by a diverse syndicate of banks. This facility expires in May 2020 and as of the date of this filing, the Company has no outstanding balances under this facility. Additionally in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, CSX issued a total of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$2.2 billion
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;of new long-term debt,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$1.4 billion
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;of which was used to repay outstanding debt, to capitalize on the lower interest rate environment. CSX uses current cash balances for general corporate purposes, which may include repayment of additional indebtedness outstanding from time to time, repurchases of CSX's common stock, capital investments, working capital requirements and improvements in productivity and other cost reduction initiatives. See Note 9, Debt and Credit Agreements.&#160;
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:13PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	In September 2016, the Company renewed and modified its existing receivables securitization facility. The facility was extended with a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	-year term scheduled to expire in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	September 2019
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	. It was modified to provide liquidity of up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$200 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, changed from the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$250 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, along with modifications to other terms. The purpose of this facility is to provide an alternative to commercial paper and a low cost source of short-term liquidity. Under the terms of this facility, CSXT transfers eligible third-party receivables to CSX Trade Receivables, a bankruptcy-remote special purpose subsidiary. A separate subsidiary of CSX services the receivables. Upon transfer, the receivables become assets of CSX Trade Receivables and are not available to the creditors of CSX or any of its other subsidiaries. In the event CSX Trade Receivables draws under this facility, the Company will record an equivalent amount of debt on its consolidated financial statements. As of the date of this filing, the Company has no outstanding balances under this facility.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">

<A NAME="eolPage44"></A>
<DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	CSX CORPORATION
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	PART II
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Working capital can also be considered a measure of a company&#8217;s ability to meet its short-term needs.&#160;&#160;CSX had a working capital
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	surplus
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$447 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;at December
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$888 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;(after reclassification of current deferred taxes) at December
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	.&#160;This decrease since the prior year end is primarily due to an increase in long-term debt maturing within a year of $311 million and cash from operations used for property additions, share repurchases and dividend payments.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	The Company&#8217;s working capital balance varies due to factors such as the timing of scheduled debt payments and changes in cash and cash equivalent balances as discussed above.&#160;Although the Company currently has a surplus, a working capital deficit is not unusual for CSX or other companies in the industry and does not indicate a lack of liquidity. The Company continues to maintain adequate current assets to satisfy current liabilities and maturing obligations when they come due.&#160;Furthermore, CSX has sufficient financial capacity, including its revolving credit facility, trade receivable facility and shelf registration statement to manage its day-to-day cash requirements and any anticipated obligations.&#160;The Company from time to time accesses the credit markets for additional liquidity.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Credit Ratings
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Credit ratings reflect an independent agency&#8217;s judgment on the likelihood that a borrower will repay a debt obligation at maturity.&#160;&#160;The ratings reflect many considerations, such as the nature of the borrower&#8217;s industry and its competitive position, the size of the company, its liquidity and access to capital and the sensitivity of a company&#8217;s cash flows to changes in the economy.&#160;&#160;The two largest rating agencies, Standard &amp; Poor&#8217;s Ratings Services (&#8220;S&amp;P&#8221;) and Moody&#8217;s Investors Service (&#8220;Moody&#8217;s&#8221;), use alphanumeric codes to designate their ratings.&#160;&#160;The highest quality rating for long-term credit obligations is AAA and Aaa for S&amp;P and Moody&#8217;s, respectively.&#160;&#160;A credit rating is not a recommendation to buy, sell or hold securities and may be subject to revision or withdrawal at any time by the assigning rating agency.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	The cost and availability of unsecured financing are materially affected by CSX's long-term credit ratings. CSX's credit ratings remained stable during
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	. As of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	December 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	December 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, S&amp;P's long-term rating on CSX was BBB+ (Stable), and Moody's was Baa1 (Stable). Ratings of BBB- and Baa3 or better by S&amp;P and Moody&#8217;s, respectively, reflect ratings on debt obligations that fall within a band of credit quality considered to be investment grade. If CSX's credit ratings were to decline to below investment grade levels, the Company could experience significant increases in its interest cost for new debt.&#160;&#160;In addition, a decline in CSX&#8217;s credit ratings to below investment grade levels could adversely affect the market&#8217;s demand, and thus the Company&#8217;s ability to readily issue new debt.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
	CSX 2016 Form 10-K p.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
	&#32;44
</FONT>

<DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	CSX CORPORATION
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	PART II
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Free Cash Flow (Non-GAAP Measure)
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Free cash flow is considered a non-GAAP financial measure under SEC Regulation G
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#32;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	and Reg S-K Item 10(e)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Management believes that free cash flow is useful to investors as it is important in evaluating the Company&#8217;s financial performance. More specifically, free cash flow measures cash generated by the business after reinvestment. This measure represents cash available for both equity and bond investors to be used for dividends, share repurchases or principal reduction on outstanding debt. Free cash flow should be considered in addition to, rather than a substitute for, cash provided by operating activities.&#160;Free cash flow is calculated by using net cash from operations and adjusting for property additions and certain other investing activities. Free cash flow before dividends
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	decreased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$145 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;year-over-year to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$847 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	. The decrease in free cash flow from the prior year is primarily due to voluntary contributions to the Company's qualified pension plans of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$250 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;in 2016, partially offset by lower property additions of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$164 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	The following table reconciles cash provided by operating activities (GAAP measure) to free cash flow (non-GAAP measure).&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
</DIV>

	Property additions include investments related to reimbursable public-private partnerships. These partnership investments of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:8PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	$41 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:8PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:8PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	$14 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:8PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:8PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	$8 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:8PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#32;in 2016, 2015 and 2014, respectively, are projects that are partially or wholly reimbursed to CSX through either government grants or other funding sources such as cash received from a property sale.&#160; These reimbursements may not be fully received in a given year; therefore, the timing of receipts may differ from the timing of the investment.&#160;Also, property additions for 2016 above do not include $307 million for locomotives purchased in 2015 using seller financing with payment made in 2016.
</FONT>

	The preparation of financial statements in conformity with accounting principles generally accepted in the United States requires that management make estimates in reporting the amounts of certain assets and liabilities, the disclosure of contingent assets and liabilities at the date of the financial statements and certain revenues and expenses during the reporting period.&#160;&#160;Actual results may differ from those estimates. These estimates and assumptions are discussed with the Audit Committee of the Board of Directors on a regular basis.&#160;&#160;Consistent with the prior year, significant estimates using management judgment are made for the following areas:

<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP;">
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	income taxes.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#160;
</FONT>
</DIV>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Casualty, Environmental and Legal Reserves
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Casualty
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Casualty reserves of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$229 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$269 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, respectively, represent accruals for personal injury, occupational disease and occupational injury claims. A majority of the casualty reserves relate to personal injuries. The Company's self-insured retention amount for these claims is $50 million per occurrence.&#160;Currently, no individual claim is expected to exceed the self-insured retention amount.&#160;In accordance with the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Contingencies Topic
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;in the ASC, to the extent the value of an individual claim exceeds the self-insured retention amount, the Company would present the liability on a gross basis with a corresponding receivable for insurance recoveries. These reserves fluctuate based upon the timing of payments as well as changes in estimate. Actual results may vary from estimates due to the number, type and severity of the injury, costs of medical treatments and uncertainties in litigation. Most of the Company's casualty claims relate to CSXT unless otherwise noted below.&#160;Defense and processing costs, which historically have been insignificant and are anticipated to be insignificant in the future, are not included in the recorded liabilities.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Personal Injury
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Personal Injury reserves of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$170 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$204 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, represent liabilities for employee work-related and third-party injuries. Work-related injuries for CSXT employees are primarily subject to FELA.&#160;&#160;In addition to FELA liabilities, employees of other current or former CSX subsidiaries are covered by various state workers&#8217; compensation laws, the Federal Longshore and Harbor Workers&#8217; Compensation Program or the Maritime Jones Act.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	CSXT retains an independent actuary to assist management in assessing the value of personal injury claims.&#160;&#160;An analysis is performed by the actuary quarterly and is reviewed by management. The methodology used by the actuary includes a development factor to reflect growth or reduction in the value of these personal injury claims. It is based largely on CSXT's historical claims and settlement experience.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	As a direct result of improvements in safety in recent years, the Company has experienced a downward trend in the severity of injuries which has resulted in a decrease in the estimate of costs per incident. During 2016, the Company reduced casualty reserves, primarily personal injury reserves, by $28 million, resulting in after-tax effect on earnings from continuing operations and net earnings of $18 million and an after-tax effect on earnings per share of $0.02. The personal injury reserve reductions were included in materials, supplies and other on the consolidated income statements. During 2015 and 2014, there were no significant changes in estimate recorded to adjust casualty reserves.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
	CSX 2016 Form 10-K p.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
	&#32;47
</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	CSX CORPORATION
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	PART II
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-LEFT:4PX;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Critical Accounting Estimates,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#32;continued
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Occupational
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Occupational reserves of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$59 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$65 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, respectively, represent liabilities for occupational disease claims and occupational injury claims. Occupational disease claims arise primarily from allegations of exposure to asbestos in the workplace. Occupational injury claims arise from allegations of exposure to certain other materials in the workplace, such as solvents, soaps, chemicals (collectively referred to as &#8220;irritants&#8221;) and diesel fuels (like exhaust fumes) or allegations of chronic physical injuries resulting from work conditions, such as repetitive stress injuries. The Company has experienced a downward trend in the number of occupational claims and reserves for these claims have decreased to a level that is no longer material to the Company's financial condition, results of operations or liquidity.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Environmental
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Environmental reserves were
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$95 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	$82 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	, respectively. The Company is a party to various proceedings related to environmental issues, including administrative and judicial proceedings involving private parties and regulatory agencies. The Company has been identified as a potentially responsible party at approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	222
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;environmentally impaired sites.&#160;&#160;Many of these are, or may be, subject to remedial action under the federal Comprehensive Environmental Response, Compensation and Liability Act of 1980 ("CERCLA"), also known as the Superfund Law, or similar state statutes.&#160;&#160;Most of these proceedings arose from environmental conditions on properties used for ongoing or discontinued railroad operations.&#160;&#160;A number of these proceedings, however, are based on allegations that the Company, or its predecessors, sent hazardous substances to facilities owned or operated by others for treatment, recycling or disposal.&#160;&#160;In addition, some of the Company&#8217;s land holdings were leased to others for commercial or industrial uses that may have resulted in releases of hazardous substances or other regulated materials onto the property and could give rise to proceedings against the Company.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	In any such proceedings, the Company is subject to environmental clean-up and enforcement actions under the Superfund Law, as well as similar state laws that may impose joint and several liability for clean-up and enforcement costs on current and former owners and operators of a site without regard to fault or the legality of the original conduct.&#160;&#160;These costs could be substantial.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	In accordance with the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Asset Retirement and Environmental Obligations Topic
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;in the ASC, the Company reviews its role with respect to each site identified at least quarterly, giving consideration to a number of factors such as:
</FONT>
</DIV>
<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="PADDING-TOP:8PX;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN; FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:72PX;">
</TD>
<TD>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP">
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:11PT;PADDING-LEFT:48PX;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#8226;
</FONT>
</DIV>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP;">
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	type of clean-up required;
</FONT>
</DIV>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<A NAME="FIS_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE_24"></A>
<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="PADDING-TOP:8PX;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN; FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:72PX;">
</TD>
<TD>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP">
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:11PT;PADDING-LEFT:48PX;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#8226;
</FONT>
</DIV>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP;">
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	nature of the Company&#8217;s alleged connection to the location (e.g., generator of waste sent to the site or owner or operator of the site);
</FONT>
</DIV>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="PADDING-TOP:8PX;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN; FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:72PX;">
</TD>
<TD>
</TD>
</TR>

<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	extent of the Company&#8217;s alleged connection (e.g., volume of waste sent to the location and other relevant factors); and
</FONT>
</DIV>

	number, connection and financial viability of other named and unnamed potentially responsible parties at the location.
